parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The emergency brake will not disengage
the alarm sounds
the vehicle rolls or moves forward while stopped
the dashboard displays warning lights and error messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes do not work properly
the vehicle slides or continues moving when the brakes are pressed
a grinding sound comes from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Caliper failure can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The caliper fails
damaging the rotor
the brake pads wear out prematurely
a grinding sound comes from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, slow down, or not start at all, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
slows down
or won't start; the battery drains frequently; the electrical system service required warning light appears; the four-wheel drive system service required warning light appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to false warnings, which can distract the driver and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The airbag system service required light comes on and off constantly while driving or parked; the passenger seat is reported to be wet
but the floor is not.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sensor and Engine Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sensor and engine control module can cause the vehicle to jerk or lose speed, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks when coming to a stop; the check engine soon light illuminates; the engine loses speed; the vehicle decreases in speed while driving on the highway; the foot pressing down on the gas pedal does not accelerate the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can lead to failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
inconsistent or faulty airbag system performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can lead to loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal does not respond
brakes fail to engage
especially on wet pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defects in the seatbelt system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Middle row seatbelts are different sizes
causing passengers to get stuck if they put the latch in the wrong one.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the running board clips can lead to cosmetic damage and potentially affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: Running board clips on the passenger side keep breaking.
